4
00:01:37,550 --> 00:01:38,720
[Haicheng Everyday]
Hello, everyone.

5
00:01:38,910 --> 00:01:39,360
Today,

6
00:01:39,440 --> 00:01:40,640
the cooks for a steel factory

7
00:01:40,670 --> 00:01:41,720
mistakenly used nitrite

8
00:01:41,800 --> 00:01:42,830
as table salt,

9
00:01:43,080 --> 00:01:44,640
resulting in 236 workers hospitalized

10
00:01:44,720 --> 00:01:45,720
for food poisoning

11
00:01:45,720 --> 00:01:46,720
after lunch.

12
00:01:46,830 --> 00:01:48,090
The workers

13
00:01:48,090 --> 00:01:49,600
have now been treated.

14
00:01:49,880 --> 00:01:51,360
We believe they'll get better soon.

15
00:01:51,750 --> 00:01:52,720
This has been Haicheng Everyday.

16
00:01:52,720 --> 00:01:53,230
I'm Sun Zeli,

17
00:01:53,230 --> 00:01:54,030
reporting in from Haicheng Hospital

18
00:01:54,030 --> 00:01:55,270
with the latest updates.

19
00:01:55,680 --> 00:01:57,020
Do you feel better?

20
00:01:59,080 --> 00:01:59,820
How do you feel?

21
00:02:03,440 --> 00:02:04,270
It's quite hard

22
00:02:04,720 --> 00:02:05,720
to be a healthcare worker.

23
00:02:06,110 --> 00:02:06,640
Yes.

24
00:02:07,550 --> 00:02:08,670
Not everyone

25
00:02:08,670 --> 00:02:09,640
can be a healthcare worker.

26
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:11,550
Let's head back and edit the footage

27
00:02:14,030 --> 00:02:15,500
and write them a good article.

28
00:02:22,040 --> 00:02:22,480
Ms. Hua.

29
00:02:22,550 --> 00:02:24,520
I heard you
took the storage's Methylene Blue

30
00:02:24,550 --> 00:02:25,830
to Haicheng Hospital.

31
00:02:26,640 --> 00:02:27,240
And then?

32
00:02:28,870 --> 00:02:29,670
And...

33
00:02:30,990 --> 00:02:32,040
they all got better

34
00:02:32,430 --> 00:02:33,040
after being injected with it.

35
00:02:33,150 --> 00:02:34,360
I'm not asking about this.

36
00:02:34,960 --> 00:02:36,080
You brought out something vital

37
00:02:36,080 --> 00:02:37,800
during an important moment.

38
00:02:37,920 --> 00:02:38,710
Ms. Su...

39
00:02:38,990 --> 00:02:40,150
She paid.

40
00:02:40,270 --> 00:02:41,550
Who cares about the money?

41
00:02:42,110 --> 00:02:42,870
It's a great chance,

42
00:02:42,920 --> 00:02:43,830
yet you wasted it.

43
00:02:44,040 --> 00:02:44,480
Fool.

44
00:02:45,550 --> 00:02:46,430
Still, Ms. Hua,

45
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:48,480
I saved a lot of people today.

46
00:02:48,720 --> 00:02:49,790
Is it better?

47
00:03:01,320 --> 00:03:02,430
How is it over here?

48
00:03:03,120 --> 00:03:04,160
Eat slowly.

49
00:03:11,740 --> 00:03:14,820
[Emergency]

50
00:03:45,300 --> 00:03:47,390
[Bu Ruotian]

51
00:03:47,390 --> 00:03:48,590
I saw the news report.

52
00:03:49,320 --> 00:03:49,960
Congratulations.

53
00:03:53,040 --> 00:03:53,590
Li,

54
00:03:54,760 --> 00:03:56,240
you're doing much better than I did.

55
00:04:09,320 --> 00:04:09,870
Li,

56
00:04:10,990 --> 00:04:12,550
you're doing much better than I did.

57
00:04:23,980 --> 00:04:26,780
[Episode 13]
[Mass Incident II - Hysteria]

58
00:04:42,790 --> 00:04:44,640
Why are you laughing so loudly?

59
00:04:45,150 --> 00:04:47,000
Yun, you're up.

60
00:04:49,120 --> 00:04:50,320
Show it to me.

61
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:56,760
Was it that chaotic then?

62
00:04:58,120 --> 00:04:58,910
Why do I look so haggard?

63
00:04:59,270 --> 00:04:59,830
Wait, Yun.

64
00:04:59,910 --> 00:05:01,270
It was a little messy at first,

65
00:05:01,440 --> 00:05:02,000
but through

66
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:03,230
your heroic guidance,

67
00:05:03,390 --> 00:05:04,520
you were in control of everything.

68
00:05:04,830 --> 00:05:06,080
Later on are all moments of your glory.

69
00:05:06,390 --> 00:05:06,990
Is that so?

70
00:05:09,380 --> 00:05:11,030
[Many workers suffering
from nitrite shock]

71
00:05:11,030 --> 00:05:12,080
I have a new idea.

72
00:05:12,150 --> 00:05:12,830
You want to use
an interventional needle?

73
00:05:14,790 --> 00:05:16,140
I look like a dog running here

74
00:05:16,140 --> 00:05:17,230
while you call that moment of my glory?

75
00:05:17,320 --> 00:05:18,430
How cute.

76
00:05:18,560 --> 00:05:19,710
It's really glorious later.

77
00:05:19,790 --> 00:05:20,230
Later on...

78
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:21,760
The series of injections...

79
00:05:21,960 --> 00:05:22,710
All were filmed?

80
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:23,590
It was very cool.

81
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:25,960
Look.

82
00:05:26,590 --> 00:05:27,200
Cool, right?

83
00:05:27,910 --> 00:05:28,590
Look.

84
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:32,270
Dr. Su,

85
00:05:32,390 --> 00:05:33,830
what have you learned from this rescue?

86
00:05:33,830 --> 00:05:34,560
Dr. Su!

87
00:05:35,590 --> 00:05:36,560
Look, you fainted.

88
00:05:37,760 --> 00:05:39,280
Yun.

89
00:05:39,790 --> 00:05:40,320
Yun.

90
00:05:40,590 --> 00:05:41,290
Yun.

91
00:05:41,680 --> 00:05:42,270
Yun.

92
00:05:47,910 --> 00:05:48,470
It was you.

93
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:50,330
No, no.

94
00:05:50,640 --> 00:05:52,390
Let me teach you again
how to administer first aid.

95
00:05:52,440 --> 00:05:53,440
How is it done?

96
00:05:53,480 --> 00:05:54,350
Wait.

97
00:05:54,350 --> 00:05:55,080
No way.

98
00:05:55,230 --> 00:05:55,910
I can't.

99
00:05:57,230 --> 00:05:58,000
Did you hear something?

100
00:05:58,560 --> 00:05:59,390
What is it?

101
00:05:59,440 --> 00:06:00,120
Bad news, Dr. Su!

102
00:06:00,120 --> 00:06:01,370
We have another wave
of poisoned patients.

103
00:06:01,370 --> 00:06:03,080
Why are there more? I...

104
00:06:03,120 --> 00:06:03,760
Get up now.

105
00:06:07,150 --> 00:06:08,120
Make way.

106
00:06:08,710 --> 00:06:09,150
Hurry.

107
00:06:09,960 --> 00:06:10,790
Move aside.

108
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:12,200
Why aren't their faces blue?

109
00:06:12,910 --> 00:06:13,470
Other than vomiting,

110
00:06:13,590 --> 00:06:14,270
are there any other symptoms?

111
00:06:14,390 --> 00:06:14,880
None for now.

112
00:06:15,350 --> 00:06:15,710
Zhou,

113
00:06:15,760 --> 00:06:16,320
prepare the saline drips.

114
00:06:16,390 --> 00:06:17,230
Label the vomit samples.

115
00:06:17,270 --> 00:06:17,980
Tell the lab to hurry up

116
00:06:17,980 --> 00:06:18,440
with the bacteria cultures.

117
00:06:18,440 --> 00:06:18,940
- Hurry.
- Yes.

118
00:06:18,940 --> 00:06:20,140
- Hold on.
- How many?

119
00:06:20,350 --> 00:06:21,000
Around 50.

120
00:06:23,070 --> 00:06:23,960
500!

121
00:06:25,520 --> 00:06:26,120
500!

122
00:06:26,520 --> 00:06:27,520
Open the door, 500!

123
00:06:27,610 --> 00:06:29,830
Stop sleeping, 500!

124
00:06:30,470 --> 00:06:31,610
What? It's the middle of the night.

125
00:06:31,610 --> 00:06:32,410
Wake up.

126
00:06:32,490 --> 00:06:33,580
I know you're tired.

127
00:06:33,760 --> 00:06:34,230
I'm tired too,

128
00:06:34,230 --> 00:06:35,260
but reality is harsh.

129
00:06:35,260 --> 00:06:35,870
Left then right.

130
00:06:35,870 --> 00:06:36,680
We have another wave of patients.

131
00:06:36,760 --> 00:06:37,600
What?

132
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:38,880
Put on the left side first, then right.

133
00:06:38,910 --> 00:06:39,790
Put it on yourself.

134
00:06:40,200 --> 00:06:41,350
I said, we have another wave
of patients,

135
00:06:41,470 --> 00:06:42,470
and the number has doubled.

136
00:06:42,560 --> 00:06:43,760
It's not nitrite poisoning this time.

137
00:06:43,790 --> 00:06:44,760
Be there in ten minutes.

138
00:06:48,180 --> 00:06:49,900
[Emergency]

139
00:06:49,910 --> 00:06:50,680
Grandma.

140
00:06:50,910 --> 00:06:52,560
Grandma, why are you sick?

141
00:06:52,910 --> 00:06:53,880
Talk to me.

142
00:06:56,150 --> 00:06:56,880
Doctor,

143
00:06:57,710 --> 00:06:58,470
save my grandma.

144
00:06:58,680 --> 00:06:59,710
- Let me through.
- Save my grandma.

145
00:07:00,910 --> 00:07:01,710
Hurry.

146
00:07:02,030 --> 00:07:02,730
- Grandma.
- How are you?

147
00:07:02,830 --> 00:07:03,390
Hold on.

148
00:07:03,390 --> 00:07:04,080
The doctor's here.

149
00:07:04,080 --> 00:07:04,880
Can you hear me?

150
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:05,980
Slowly.

151
00:07:12,560 --> 00:07:13,200
Zhou Litao.

152
00:07:13,830 --> 00:07:14,230
Ms. Su.

153
00:07:14,320 --> 00:07:15,040
What's going on?

154
00:07:15,270 --> 00:07:16,830
They're family members
of the poisoned workers.

155
00:07:16,830 --> 00:07:18,570
They've all been vomiting.

156
00:07:18,570 --> 00:07:19,960
- Coming.
- The first was an old woman.

157
00:07:19,960 --> 00:07:20,810
She had severe vomiting.

158
00:07:20,880 --> 00:07:22,090
Then, the factory called us.

159
00:07:22,090 --> 00:07:23,640
They say more family members
are vomiting.

160
00:07:23,710 --> 00:07:24,810
Where's Yun?

161
00:07:25,120 --> 00:07:26,030
Looking at the scans with Zheng.

162
00:07:27,960 --> 00:07:29,120
Here, paper towels.

163
00:07:29,280 --> 00:07:30,250
Slowly.

164
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:40,200
How's the situation?

165
00:07:40,200 --> 00:07:40,750
Ms. Su.

166
00:07:40,800 --> 00:07:42,280
Is it linked to the nitrite?

167
00:07:42,390 --> 00:07:43,270
Those vomiting patients

168
00:07:43,350 --> 00:07:44,710
don't have blue-gray skin.

169
00:07:44,830 --> 00:07:45,390
Also,

170
00:07:45,470 --> 00:07:46,590
they live in the family dorms

171
00:07:46,640 --> 00:07:47,760
where most of them cook for themselves.

172
00:07:47,960 --> 00:07:48,830
That's why their food

173
00:07:48,830 --> 00:07:49,920
isn't the same as the workers'.

174
00:07:50,030 --> 00:07:50,910
What are the test results?

175
00:07:51,080 --> 00:07:51,930
We've done everything

176
00:07:51,930 --> 00:07:52,940
from blood tests and lung function tests

177
00:07:52,940 --> 00:07:53,840
to digestive tests.

178
00:07:53,840 --> 00:07:54,520
Nothing unusual was found.

179
00:07:54,960 --> 00:07:55,790
What do the other hospitals say?

180
00:07:55,830 --> 00:07:57,790
They're also looking for the cause.

181
00:07:58,230 --> 00:07:59,390
I hear the higher-ups

182
00:07:59,680 --> 00:08:00,790
now know of this matter.

183
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:02,520
Could it

184
00:08:02,590 --> 00:08:03,830
be a new viral outbreak?

185
00:08:05,270 --> 00:08:06,590
Wouldn't all of us

186
00:08:06,830 --> 00:08:07,560
be in danger then?

187
00:08:08,080 --> 00:08:08,680
Hua,

188
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:09,440
should we consider

189
00:08:09,520 --> 00:08:10,520
an emergency mobilization

190
00:08:10,710 --> 00:08:12,030
to establish a major epidemic
command center?

191
00:08:15,470 --> 00:08:16,830
The old woman's lung scans are out.

192
00:08:21,470 --> 00:08:22,200
It's not the respiratory tract.

193
00:08:22,440 --> 00:08:23,230
Nor is it the digestive tract.

194
00:08:23,390 --> 00:08:24,080
Could it

195
00:08:24,150 --> 00:08:25,120
be a bacterial infection?

196
00:08:25,320 --> 00:08:25,680
No.

197
00:08:26,030 --> 00:08:26,680
The scans are fine.

198
00:08:28,590 --> 00:08:29,710
But that old woman

199
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:31,350
is weak from vomiting.

200
00:08:32,400 --> 00:08:33,230
We've just been notified

201
00:08:33,750 --> 00:08:34,680
over 100 more family members

202
00:08:34,680 --> 00:08:35,160
of the workers

203
00:08:35,160 --> 00:08:36,080
are showing the same symptoms.

204
00:08:36,230 --> 00:08:37,280
How are the staff in contact
with the patients?

205
00:08:37,560 --> 00:08:38,800
No abnormalities yet.

206
00:08:39,350 --> 00:08:39,960
I'll head back.

207
00:08:41,960 --> 00:08:42,560
Are you okay?

208
00:08:44,470 --> 00:08:45,080
I'm fine.

209
00:08:48,750 --> 00:08:49,560
Hey, Mr. Pan.

210
00:08:50,400 --> 00:08:51,750
We're already preparing.

211
00:08:51,870 --> 00:08:53,160
Okay. Got it.

212
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:55,830
The city mayor has instructed experts

213
00:08:55,920 --> 00:08:57,230
from the guide groups to rush over

214
00:08:57,400 --> 00:08:58,920
to consult with the hospitals

215
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:00,470
so that we can
find out the cause of the illness.

216
00:09:00,990 --> 00:09:01,990
The guide group's leader

217
00:09:01,990 --> 00:09:02,710
wants our hospital

218
00:09:02,710 --> 00:09:04,080
to retrieve samples from the scene

219
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:05,110
for lab testing.

220
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:05,960
Yun,

221
00:09:06,110 --> 00:09:07,080
transfer the vomiting patients

222
00:09:07,110 --> 00:09:08,160
into the Emergency Department.

223
00:09:08,280 --> 00:09:08,960
Treat them in quarantine.

224
00:09:09,110 --> 00:09:09,510
Okay.

225
00:09:09,630 --> 00:09:10,960
Before we find the cause
of their illness,

226
00:09:11,230 --> 00:09:12,750
we'll try to stay in control

227
00:09:12,830 --> 00:09:14,320
until the experts arrive.

228
00:09:14,800 --> 00:09:16,320
Emergency Department staff
will have to work hard.

229
00:09:16,400 --> 00:09:17,630
Be on shift for 24 hours.

230
00:09:17,710 --> 00:09:18,920
No one is to go in or out
as they please.

231
00:09:18,960 --> 00:09:19,470
Yes.

232
00:09:20,280 --> 00:09:20,830
Su Yun,

233
00:09:21,110 --> 00:09:22,230
go with Chang Yue
to the patients' homes.

234
00:09:22,470 --> 00:09:23,510
Check their food.

235
00:09:23,830 --> 00:09:24,830
Perhaps we'll have some new discoveries.

236
00:09:24,920 --> 00:09:26,200
I leave the Emergency Department to you.

237
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:26,920
Be quick.

238
00:09:27,630 --> 00:09:28,280
Yue, let's go.

239
00:09:38,350 --> 00:09:38,830
Hello?

240
00:09:39,040 --> 00:09:39,470
Li,

241
00:09:39,680 --> 00:09:40,510
I heard from Mr. Pan

242
00:09:40,510 --> 00:09:41,800
the mass incident has worsened.

243
00:09:42,320 --> 00:09:43,560
We're searching for the cause.

244
00:09:43,990 --> 00:09:44,750
Don't forget to come back

245
00:09:44,870 --> 00:09:45,710
for your follow-up in five days.

246
00:09:46,160 --> 00:09:47,920
I remember. See you in five days.

247
00:09:48,230 --> 00:09:49,080
See you in five days.

248
00:10:02,360 --> 00:10:03,390
Don't move.

249
00:10:06,710 --> 00:10:07,340
Ms. Su,

250
00:10:07,470 --> 00:10:08,490
you can't move right now.

251
00:10:09,470 --> 00:10:10,250
Get a stretcher

252
00:10:10,250 --> 00:10:11,080
and send her to Emergency.

253
00:10:11,160 --> 00:10:11,930
Emergency?

254
00:10:12,630 --> 00:10:13,990
Why to the Emergency?

255
00:10:14,230 --> 00:10:15,610
I suspect
you suffered a sudden heart attack.

256
00:10:26,110 --> 00:10:27,200
500? Speak.

257
00:10:28,960 --> 00:10:30,200
What? Heart attack?

258
00:10:33,830 --> 00:10:34,890
Get operating.

259
00:10:34,960 --> 00:10:35,920
I'll handle the procedure once I'm back.

260
00:10:36,630 --> 00:10:37,160
Hey, Zheng Ren.

261
00:10:38,590 --> 00:10:39,320
Please.

262
00:10:40,590 --> 00:10:41,680
Who has a heart attack?

263
00:10:42,440 --> 00:10:43,040
Hua.

264
00:10:44,630 --> 00:10:46,230
Her heart had no issues.

265
00:10:49,230 --> 00:10:50,870
It must be due to exhaustion.

266
00:10:51,710 --> 00:10:53,040
Hua is too stubborn.

267
00:10:53,280 --> 00:10:54,200
She could have

268
00:10:54,230 --> 00:10:55,280
chosen a more carefree life.

269
00:10:57,710 --> 00:10:58,510
Do you know

270
00:10:58,590 --> 00:10:59,560
why I call her Hua?

271
00:11:03,470 --> 00:11:04,710
The hospital

272
00:11:04,800 --> 00:11:06,200
is the most painful place on earth.

273
00:11:08,110 --> 00:11:09,350
Despairing patients,

274
00:11:10,040 --> 00:11:11,320
stunned family members,

275
00:11:12,320 --> 00:11:13,590
exhausted doctors,

276
00:11:14,200 --> 00:11:15,630
and haggard nurses.

277
00:11:18,080 --> 00:11:18,830
When you're there,

278
00:11:19,800 --> 00:11:21,230
the only thing left in the mind

279
00:11:22,470 --> 00:11:23,960
is to keep living.

280
00:11:27,870 --> 00:11:30,440
Keep living, not live.

281
00:11:33,280 --> 00:11:34,710
I don't just want to survive.

282
00:11:35,440 --> 00:11:36,590
I want to live.

283
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:38,750
That's right.

284
00:11:39,830 --> 00:11:40,590
It's why

285
00:11:41,990 --> 00:11:43,800
I must doll myself up.

286
00:11:45,400 --> 00:11:46,800
I want everyone to know

287
00:11:48,110 --> 00:11:49,920
what it's like to live.

288
00:11:51,680 --> 00:11:53,510
Only by seeing the beauty in life

289
00:11:54,990 --> 00:11:56,920
can you endure the torment of living.

290
00:12:07,160 --> 00:12:07,830
Don't worry.

291
00:12:08,590 --> 00:12:09,560
She'll be fine.

292
00:12:34,830 --> 00:12:35,990
It's a family of three.

293
00:12:36,280 --> 00:12:36,870
The place is so small.

294
00:12:36,870 --> 00:12:37,630
There's not even a room divider.

295
00:12:37,630 --> 00:12:38,200
How do they live?

